Description: Rim sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery cup with slightly concave lip; glazed black on interior and exterior save for reserved band at rim on interior; inscription cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 687, no. 458, pl. 22.2.2)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1688)
